          "description": "<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><big><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\">Join</span> <strong><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\">BMW CCA Puget Sound on June 24th&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\">for our second annual Almost Solstice&nbsp;twilight HPDE at Pacific Raceways.&nbsp; Celebrate peak summer with a Wednesday&nbsp;evening driving your car on track from 4:30PM to dusk.&nbsp; Many of you have asked for an evening event.</span></big></p>\n<ul>\n<li><big>Registration begins at 3:00PM &nbsp;with the track hot at 4:30PM.&nbsp;</big></li>\n<li><big>We have 5 hours of track time so nearly the same as a daytime event at a much lower cost.</big></li>\n<li><big>This will be a full instructed HPDE, so instructors are welcome to enroll.&nbsp;&nbsp;</big></li>\n</ul>\n<p><big>So take advantage of this unique solstice opportunity.</big></p>\n<p><big><strong>Cost: $250&nbsp;for the evening,&nbsp;including dinner.&nbsp;</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong> Note: MSR has added an additional $2 fee&nbsp;per registration unless you are a Hagerty Drivers Club member.&nbsp;</big></p>\n<p><big><strong>Registration will close 4&nbsp;days prior to the event or when the event reaches capacity.</strong></big></p>\n<p><span class=\"marker\"><big><em><strong><span style=\"background-color:#ffff00\">Confirmation: You be wait listed initially and confirmed as soon as possible given run group capacity and instructor availability. You will be charged upon confirmation.&nbsp;</span></strong></em></big></span></p>\n<p><big>BMWCCA Puget Sound Region has provided High Performance Driving events at Pacific Raceway and other tracks for more than 40 years. We have a strong&nbsp;safety record and an experienced group of trained&nbsp;Instructors and staff.</big></p>\n<p><big><strong>Our Values</strong></big></p>\n<ul>\n<li><big>Safety - First and foremost.</big></li>\n<li><big>Fun</big></li>\n<li><big>Educational –&nbsp; Emphasis on improving skills.</big></li>\n<li><big>Welcoming -&nbsp;Friendly and casual.</big></li>\n<li><big>Approachable</big></li>\n<li><big>Inclusive - Open to all members with all skills and all types of cars.</big></li>\n</ul>\n<p><big>Attendees are assigned to&nbsp;run groups by the Chief Driving Instructor, based on the skills and abilities of the driver, vehicle, and other participating drivers.&nbsp; Groups run from Novice, where all drivers are instructed to Advanced/Instructors where all drivers are Solo.&nbsp; Others may be instructed or solo depending on driver skill. Passing rules vary by run group.&nbsp; Drivers are expected to advance over time with improving skills and abilities.</big></p>\n<p><big>Following time on track, run groups will meet in educational breakout sessions for discussion about the track, conditions, traffic management, driving theory, and tips for improvement.&nbsp;&nbsp;</big></p>\n<p><big>See&nbsp; <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://bmw-club-psr.org/driver-education\">https://bmw-club-psr.org/driver-education</a>&nbsp;for more information about the HPDE program.</big></p>\n<p><big><strong>Cancellation Policy:&nbsp;</strong></big></p>\n<p><big><strong>As a not-for-profit club, it is BMW CCA PSR's goal to provide exceptional events while breaking even financially. Event expenses&nbsp;are fixed and paid in advance.&nbsp; The cancellation policy for this event is as follows:</strong></big></p>\n<p><big><strong>• Cancellations received prior to two weeks before the event&nbsp;will be 100% refunded.<br>\n• No refunds or credits will be given if canceled after the time stated above or if you do not attend the event.<br>\n• It is the attendee’s responsibility to prepare and bring a vehicle that is safe for the event and meets the club’s safety and technical requirements. There will be no refunds for mechanical failure.<br>\n• No refunds will be issued due to halting an event for any reason - rain, incident, etc.</strong></big></p>",
