          "description": "<p><big><strong>On May 21st&nbsp;we will&nbsp;be hosting an advanced/intermediate only driver day.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></big></p>\n<p><big><strong>This event is open to instructors, advanced drivers and solo signed off intermediate drivers.&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><strong>We will be running two run groups for the day – and may adjust to open track based on participation and traffic as the day goes on.&nbsp; As an HPDE, breakout group discussions will be held as normal following track time and limited in-car instruction will be available as requested.&nbsp; So lots of track time in a fun, relaxed format. &nbsp;&nbsp;We hope to see you there.</strong></big></p>\n<p><big><strong>Please make sure your driving resume is up to date in MSR so that we can evaluate your solo bona fides.&nbsp; If you have any questions about your qualifications for this event, please contact cdi@bmw-club-psr.org</strong></big></p>\n<p><big><strong>Cost: $400&nbsp;for the day, including lunch.&nbsp; Note: MSR has added an additional $2 fee&nbsp;per registration unless you are a Hagerty Drivers Club member.&nbsp;</strong></big></p>\n<p><big><strong>Registration will close 5&nbsp;days prior to the event or when the event reaches capacity.</strong></big></p>\n<p><strong><big><em><span style=\"background-color:#dddddd\">Confirmation: You be wait listed initially and confirmed as soon as possible given run group capacity and instructor availability. You will be charged upon confirmation.&nbsp;</span></em></big></strong></p>\n<p><big>BMWCCA Puget Sound Region has provided driving events at Pacific Raceway and other tracks for more than 40 years. We have a very good safety record and an experienced group of volunteer&nbsp;staff.</big></p>\n<p><strong>Our Values</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Safety -First and foremost.</li>\n<li>Fun</li>\n<li>Educational –&nbsp;Emphasis on improving skills.</li>\n<li>Welcoming— Friendly and casual.</li>\n<li>Approachable</li>\n<li>Inclusive—Open to all members with all skills and all types of cars.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Attendees are assigned to run groups by the Chief Driving Instructor, based on the skills and abilities of the driver, vehicle, and other participating drivers.&nbsp; &nbsp;Passing rules run from limited to open depending on run group.&nbsp; Drivers are expected to advance over time with improving skills and abilities.</p>\n<p>Following time on track, run groups will meet in educational breakout sessions for discussion about the track, conditions, traffic management, driving theory, and tips for improvement.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>See&nbsp; <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://bmw-club-psr.org/driver-education\">https://bmw-club-psr.org/driver-education</a>&nbsp;for more information about the HPDE program.</p>\n<p>As a not-for-profit entity, it is our goal to provide exceptional events while breaking even financially. Event expenses (venue rental, corner workers, ambulance services, catering, etc.) are fixed and paid in advance. &nbsp;The cancellation policy for this event is as follows:</p>\n<p>• Cancellations received prior to two weeks before the event will be 100% refunded.<br>\n• No refunds or credits will be given if canceled after the time stated above or if you do not attend the event.<br>\n• It is the attendee’s responsibility to prepare and bring a vehicle that is safe for the event and meets the club’s safety and technical requirements. There will be no refunds for mechanical failure.<br>\n• No refunds will be issued due to halting an event for any reason - rain, incident, etc.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
